The D3D11 cache gate is confirmed: all the VS/PS selection and the reflected PS cbuffer upload, including b0, are inside `if (!cacheHit)`. On a cache hit, `apply()` returns true without touching b0. That matches the locked observation pattern: same shader/pass in adjacent draws can draw without Producer-B.
