codex
I also found a second non-Producer-B writer to PS b0: `Direct3d11_StateCache::setFog()` uploads only one float4 to `updatePS(0, &fog, sizeof(fog))`. With tail-zeroing enabled, that makes c1+ clean zero. I’m checking whether shader apply calls this per pass and whether caching can skip the later full b0 repair.
