codex
Bottom line: the most likely cause is **D3D11 static-shader caching plus a PS-b0 clobber immediately before the cached bind**. `ShaderPrimitiveSorter` calls `Graphics::setAlphaFadeOpacity()` before each pass, D3D11 writes that as a 16-byte `updatePS(0)` into the same shared b0, zeroing the tail, and then `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply()` can cache-hit and skip the full 400-byte Producer-B b0 rewrite. The next `DrawIndexed` then samples b0 c1/c3 as clean zero.

**D3D11 Chain**
- `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::Phase::draw`: per entry, calls `setLights`, `prepareToDraw`, `Graphics::setAlphaFadeOpacity`, then per pass `Graphics::setStaticShader(staticShader, i)`, then `shaderPrimitive.draw()` at `clientGraphics/src/shared/ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:718`, `:725`, `:742`, `:746`, `:781`.
- Static mesh primitive setup binds geometry in `ShaderPrimitiveSetTemplate::LocalShaderPrimitiveTemplate::prepareToDraw`: `Graphics::setVertexBuffer`, optional `Graphics::setIndexBuffer` at `ShaderPrimitiveSetTemplate.cpp:1237-1269`.
- Static mesh draw dispatch calls the stored draw function at `ShaderPrimitiveSetTemplate.cpp:1285-1288`; indexed triangle list maps through `Graphics::drawIndexedTriangleList` via the lookup table at `ShaderPrimitiveSetTemplate.cpp:673-686`.
- `Graphics::setStaticShader` validates and calls backend only if `shader.isValid()` at `Graphics.cpp:1193-1200`.
- D3D11 backend slot is wired at `Direct3d11.cpp:1041`; draw slots at `Direct3d11.cpp:1110-1115`.
- `Direct3d11_StateCache::setStaticShader` always calls `d3dShader->apply(pass)` at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:2399-2420`.
- `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData::apply` computes `cacheHit` at `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:762`; all real work is inside `if (!cacheHit)` at `:764`.
- On cache miss, it sets current VS/PS at `:782-795`, computes dot3 c0 from `worldDirectionToObjectLocal()` at `:968-980`, uploads b0 with `updatePS(layout.BindPoint, staging, layout.TotalSize)` at `:1427`, and writes the legacy shadow back at `:1434-1436`.
- `updatePS` maps the one shared PS slot buffer with `D3D11_MAP_WRITE_DISCARD`, zeroes the whole max buffer when `P19_CBUF_ZERO_TAIL` is on, copies `sizeBytes`, and unmaps at `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.cpp:194-216`; bind is `PSSetConstantBuffers` at `:233-240`.
- Final draw path calls `applyPreDrawState`, binds shaders/cbuffers/SRVs at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1203-1376`, then `DrawIndexed` for indexed triangle list at `:3082-3086`.

**Short-Circuit / Skip Points**
- `Graphics::setStaticShader` skips backend apply when `shader.isValid()` is false; draw wrappers also skip when `ms_shaderValidated` is false (`Graphics.cpp:1197-1200`, `:3095-3099`).
- D3D11 `apply()` cache hit skips Producer-B entirely: `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:762-764`, then returns pass validity at `:1724-1726`. This is the critical “draw without fresh b0 rewrite” path.
- `apply()` also skips individual reflected cbuffer layouts when `TotalSize == 0` or suspiciously huge (`:855-887`), but locked probes say bump b0 is `BindPoint==0/TotalSize==400` and applies are good when they run.
- `applyPreDrawState()` can skip the draw on null context, unresolved shaders, null VS, or null layout (`Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1203-1224` and nearby). These do not explain a black submitted asset-PS draw; they prevent the draw.
- PS bind may choose native/rewritten/fallback at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1317-1356`; that changes shader lane, not c1/c3 being zero in the same asset PS.
- Separate b0 clobber: `Direct3d11_StateCache::setAlphaFadeOpacity` writes only one float4 to PS slot 0 at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:2022-2028`. Because `P19_CBUF_ZERO_TAIL` is enabled at `Direct3d11_ConstantBuffer.cpp:38` and `updatePS` zeroes before copying at `:208-214`, this makes b0 c1+ zero. `setFog` has the same bug class at `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1908-1920`.

**Per-Object Dot3 Dependency**
The D3D11 b0 dot3 block is per-object only for c0: `worldDirectionToObjectLocal()` uses the cached object transform (`Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:1956-1958`, `:2003-2007`). But when Producer-B runs, it rewrites the whole c0..c4 block together (`Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:975-980`). There is no path where c0 is refreshed but c1..c4 are intentionally skipped inside Producer-B. The failure is that Producer-B does not run on cache hit after b0 was clobbered.

**D3D9 Contrast**
- D3D9 has static shader caching too (`Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:1045-1065`), so the brief would be inaccurate if it implied “no D3D9 shader cache.”
- But D3D9 applies lights from the draw path: `drawIndexedPrimitive()` calls `drawPrimitive()` at `Direct3d9.cpp:4137-4148`; `drawPrimitive()` calls `Direct3d9_LightManager::selectLights()` before GPU draw at `Direct3d9.cpp:3999-4012`.
- `selectLights()` applies `applyLights_vertexShader()` or `applyLights_vertexShader_dot3()` at `Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:489-503`.
- `applyLights_vertexShader_dot3()` computes object-local direction and writes `PSCR_dot3LightDirection` for 5 registers at `Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:768-830`; the register enum maps c0..c4 at `Direct3d9_PixelShaderConstantRegisters.h:23-27`.
- D3D9 alpha fade is folded into the dot3 light payload, not a separate b0 overwrite: see `Direct3d9.cpp:3579-3605`, `:4074-4077`, and `Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:795-830`.

So the single best answer is: **some bump draws are cache misses and get the full Producer-B b0 sun upload; others are cache hits after `setAlphaFadeOpacity()` has overwritten shared PS b0 slot 0 with a 16-byte payload and zeroed c1/c3/c4, so they draw black.**
